Heat the oil and butter in a saucepan. Add the potato, parsnip, garlic and thyme for five minutes over a gentle heat.Add the stock, salt and freshly ground black pepper. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10-15 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender.Add the yoghurt and Stilton and blend with a hand blender until smooth.Return to the heat and add a splash of milk. Serve warm.